The paper deals with maintaining a minimum cost set cover under element insertions and deletions, which is a problem in data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.AL). The primal-dual approach used in the paper is a common technique in optimization (cs.DM) and game theory (cs.GT). The paper also involves analyzing the approximation ratio of the algorithm, which is related to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG).
